♪ Ben 10! ♪

00:12.542 --> 00:13.625
♪ Ben 10! ♪

00:13.708 --> 00:14.875
♪ Ben 10! ♪

00:14.958 --> 00:16.792
♪ Ben 10! ♪

00:16.875 --> 00:18.958
♪ Ben 10! ♪

00:22.208 --> 00:27.750
♪♪

00:27.833 --> 00:31.208
[ Singing guitar notes ]

00:31.292 --> 00:33.185
- MAX: Okay, - it's been two hours.

00:33.292 --> 00:34.977
- -Aww! - -The rules of the road say

00:35.083 --> 00:36.769
- We change the music - every two hours.

00:36.875 --> 00:38.519
- It's my turn - to pick the station.

00:38.625 --> 00:40.977
MAN:

00:38.625 --> 00:43.375
<i>World Harmony.</i>

00:41.001 --> 00:43.458
<i>You're listening to 98.6...</i>

00:43.458 --> 00:46.708
[ Marimba playing ]

00:46.792 --> 00:48.458
Ah!

00:48.542 --> 00:50.083
Relaxing.

00:50.167 --> 00:51.208
Ugh!

00:51.292 --> 00:53.040
I hate World Harmony.

00:53.064 --> 00:54.833
So boring and weird!

00:54.917 --> 00:56.042
Oh, come on!

00:56.125 --> 00:57.476
- Just because it's different - doesn't mean

00:57.500 --> 00:59.019
- You can't learn - something from it.

00:59.125 --> 01:00.769
- It's gonna learn me - into a nap.

01:00.875 --> 01:03.143
- I don't understand why you - just couldn't leave the station

01:03.167 --> 01:04.583
For a few more minutes.

01:04.667 --> 01:05.875
Rules of the road...

01:05.958 --> 01:07.810
- You had your turn - and now it's my turn.

01:07.917 --> 01:09.123
Ugh, you have

01:09.147 --> 01:10.375
so many weird rules!

01:10.458 --> 01:12.352
- And how does that - make you feel, Ben?

01:12.458 --> 01:13.810
I feel like... wait!

01:13.834 --> 01:15.208
Gwen, what are you doing?

01:15.292 --> 01:16.290
I can see you two

01:16.314 --> 01:17.333
have unresolved tension,

01:17.417 --> 01:18.644
so I'm going to resolve it,

01:18.668 --> 01:19.917
with psychology.

01:20.000 --> 01:21.167
Please, continue.

01:21.250 --> 01:22.601
- He's always telling me - what to do,

01:22.625 --> 01:23.727
Like don't chew

01:23.751 --> 01:24.875
with your mouth open...

01:24.958 --> 01:26.292
<i>Ben!</i>

01:26.375 --> 01:28.059
- Or don't put your face - so close to the screen!

01:28.083 --> 01:29.373
<i>Ben!</i>

01:28.083 --> 01:30.708
as Heatblast.

01:29.397 --> 01:30.792
Or don't cook food

01:30.792 --> 01:32.875
[ Laughs ]

01:32.958 --> 01:33.833
<i>Ben!</i>

01:33.917 --> 01:35.167
I've had it!

01:35.250 --> 01:36.601
- Ben, I'm not telling you - what to do,

01:36.625 --> 01:38.125
I'm giving you advice.

01:38.208 --> 01:39.435
I don't just make this stuff up

01:39.459 --> 01:40.708
to keep you from having fun.

01:40.792 --> 01:42.644
My advice serves a purpose

01:42.668 --> 01:44.542
and... rules of the road!

01:44.625 --> 01:44.625
- Aah! - No yelling

01:44.625 --> 01:46.417
In the Rustbucket!

01:46.500 --> 01:47.936
Uh, guys, the key

01:47.960 --> 01:49.417
to resolving any conflict

01:49.500 --> 01:50.750
is good communication.

01:50.833 --> 01:51.935
I'm a kid on a road trip

01:51.959 --> 01:53.083
across the country.

01:53.167 --> 01:54.311
I'm supposed to be

01:54.335 --> 01:55.500
having fun here!

01:55.583 --> 01:57.208
Let me live!

01:57.292 --> 01:58.519
Do you think I like to

01:58.543 --> 01:59.792
just boss you around for fun?

01:59.875 --> 02:01.519
- You never - listen to me.

02:01.625 --> 02:02.894
I can see this is gonna be

02:02.918 --> 02:04.208
my toughest case yet.

02:04.292 --> 02:05.809
- I don't just boss you - around all the time!

02:05.833 --> 02:07.227
-Yeah, yeah, you do.

02:07.251 --> 02:08.667
-Oh, for crying out loud!

02:10.292 --> 02:11.540
Uh, I think it would be better

02:11.564 --> 02:12.833
for your personal development

02:12.917 --> 02:13.936
if you stayed

02:13.960 --> 02:15.000
and talked about this.

02:15.083 --> 02:16.935
- No aliening - while you're out.

02:17.042 --> 02:18.167
BEN: Whatever!

02:18.250 --> 02:19.770
- Well, if you want - to talk about it.

02:19.833 --> 02:21.167
I need a nap.

02:21.250 --> 02:22.665
Ah, at least I can listen

02:22.689 --> 02:24.125
to my music in peace.

02:24.708 --> 02:28.167
[ Humming ]

02:29.125 --> 02:30.331
"No aliening

02:30.355 --> 02:31.583
while you're out."

02:31.667 --> 02:33.082
Well, I think that aliening

02:33.106 --> 02:34.542
right now is a good idea.

02:34.625 --> 02:37.208
And he'll never find out anyway.

02:40.333 --> 02:42.060
I don't see why... Nuh!

02:42.084 --> 02:43.833
He can't just... Nuh!

02:43.917 --> 02:45.561
Let me do... Uh!

02:45.585 --> 02:47.250
What I want!

02:47.333 --> 02:50.292
Aah!

02:50.375 --> 02:51.498
I don't get it.

02:51.522 --> 02:52.667
It's a beautiful night out.

02:52.750 --> 02:54.206
I'm a genius with the ability

02:54.230 --> 02:55.708
to manipulate animals,

02:55.792 --> 02:57.415
flying through the sky

02:57.439 --> 02:59.083
on a creature that I can control

02:59.167 --> 03:01.623
by simply focusing my thoughts

03:01.647 --> 03:04.125
on a simple echolocation device.

03:04.208 --> 03:05.665
I should be happy.

03:05.689 --> 03:07.167
So why aren't I?

03:07.250 --> 03:09.167
Perhaps I need a new life goal.

03:09.250 --> 03:10.415
I just finished this

03:10.439 --> 03:11.625
new transforming gun,

03:11.708 --> 03:13.685
and I did have a plan to

03:13.709 --> 03:15.708
transform humanity into animals.

03:15.792 --> 03:17.000
But you know what?

03:17.083 --> 03:18.519
Maybe it's time

03:18.543 --> 03:20.000
for a whole new animal.

03:20.083 --> 03:21.623
Maybe I'll even move on

03:21.647 --> 03:23.208
from that Tennyson brat.

03:23.292 --> 03:25.375
[ Screams ]

03:27.083 --> 03:29.456
Tennyson first,

03:29.480 --> 03:31.875
new life plans second.

03:33.875 --> 03:35.331
Oh, hey, Ben. I saw quite

03:35.355 --> 03:36.833
a few fireballs out there.

03:36.917 --> 03:37.936
Everything okay?

03:37.960 --> 03:39.000
-Everything's great.

03:39.083 --> 03:40.081
As a matter of fact,

03:40.105 --> 03:41.125
I broke a dumb rule,

03:41.208 --> 03:42.519
I feel a lot better,

03:42.543 --> 03:43.875
and nothing bad happened.

03:43.958 --> 03:45.185
It's just the opposite

03:45.209 --> 03:46.458
of what Grandpa said.

03:46.542 --> 03:47.583
[ Whimpers ]

03:47.667 --> 03:48.875
Ha-ha, very funny.

03:48.958 --> 03:50.519
No, Ben, watch out!

03:50.543 --> 03:52.125
Duck!

03:52.208 --> 03:54.250
[ Panting ]

03:54.333 --> 03:56.417
That's right, run!

03:59.958 --> 04:01.185
Dr. Animo?

04:01.209 --> 04:02.458
What's he doing here?

04:02.542 --> 04:03.893
- [ Chuckles nervously ] - No problem, though,

04:03.917 --> 04:05.123
Because Diamondhead's

04:05.147 --> 04:06.375
here to...

04:06.458 --> 04:08.352
- -You were saying? - -Whoa!

04:08.458 --> 04:10.477
I truly meant to change

04:10.501 --> 04:12.542
my ways, Tennyson,

04:12.625 --> 04:13.873
but you just had to

04:13.897 --> 04:15.167
singe my eyebrows off.

04:15.250 --> 04:16.436
Okay, maybe I messed up

04:16.460 --> 04:17.667
a little there.

04:17.750 --> 04:19.623
But in my defense, my fireball

04:19.647 --> 04:21.542
hitting Animo was 100% accident.

04:21.625 --> 04:22.958
Whoa!

04:23.042 --> 04:23.042
- He's really - into World Harmony.

04:23.042 --> 04:25.000
[ Snoring ]

04:25.083 --> 04:26.102
How do you sleep

04:26.126 --> 04:27.167
through a bat attack?

04:27.250 --> 04:29.583
[ Groans ]

04:29.667 --> 04:30.873
Kiss your

04:30.897 --> 04:32.125
humanity good-bye!

04:32.208 --> 04:33.833
[ All grunting ]

04:33.917 --> 04:35.602
Last time I work with

04:35.626 --> 04:37.333
a free-spirited bat monster.

04:37.417 --> 04:38.894
Oh, what a racket!

04:38.918 --> 04:40.417
I told you kids to...

04:40.500 --> 04:42.542
Ben?

04:42.625 --> 04:44.625
[ Shrieks ]

04:44.708 --> 04:48.500
Oh! E-E-Easy there.

04:48.583 --> 04:50.269
- Uh, there's a bat - out there.

04:50.375 --> 04:51.436
The bat likes

04:51.460 --> 04:52.542
World Harmony?

04:52.625 --> 04:54.458
Bye-bye, brats!

04:54.542 --> 04:57.125
Look out!

04:57.208 --> 04:58.667
[ Grunts ]

04:58.750 --> 05:00.167
[ Plink! ]

05:00.250 --> 05:01.519
-Grandpa!

05:01.543 --> 05:02.833
-Was that a chicken ray?

05:02.917 --> 05:04.143
- What sort of question - is that?!

05:04.167 --> 05:05.894
- Of course - it's a chicken ray!

05:06.000 --> 05:08.458
[ Clucking ]

05:10.833 --> 05:13.625
Grandpa, come back!

05:13.708 --> 05:15.394
- We need to come up - with a plan, stat!

05:15.500 --> 05:16.769
-Split up?

05:16.793 --> 05:18.083
-Right!

05:18.167 --> 05:19.790
Hey, Animo, over here,

05:19.814 --> 05:21.458
you crafty, evil genius.

05:21.542 --> 05:22.540
Splitting up, eh?

05:22.564 --> 05:23.583
Fine!

05:23.667 --> 05:25.042
I'll take care of you

05:25.125 --> 05:26.644
and let my creature

05:26.668 --> 05:28.208
take care of the other brat!

05:28.292 --> 05:32.625
[ Clucking ]

05:35.208 --> 05:37.625
Bawk, bawk, Grandpa Max?!

05:37.708 --> 05:40.708
Hey, I'm sorry about earlier.

05:40.792 --> 05:42.875
Aah!

05:42.958 --> 05:46.083
[ Shrieks ]

05:48.042 --> 05:49.269
What do I know about

05:49.293 --> 05:50.542
defeating giant bats?

05:50.625 --> 05:53.083
Absolutely nothing!

05:55.000 --> 05:56.625
[ Roars ]

05:56.708 --> 05:58.583
[ Grunts ]

05:58.667 --> 06:00.875
Ha-ha!

06:03.333 --> 06:06.248
Hey, flap-face, let's see how

06:06.272 --> 06:09.208
you feel about your odds... now!

06:09.292 --> 06:10.290
Heard of fighting

06:10.314 --> 06:11.333
fire with fire?!

06:11.417 --> 06:13.894
Same goes for fighting

06:13.918 --> 06:16.417
bats with bats!

06:16.500 --> 06:18.269
And that's out of the park!

06:18.293 --> 06:20.083
[ Chuckles ]

06:20.167 --> 06:22.060
- Huh, okay. - Batting didn't work.

06:22.167 --> 06:24.102
- Maybe it's time - to do some pitching!

06:24.208 --> 06:27.750
♪♪

06:27.833 --> 06:29.958
[ Shrieks ]

06:30.042 --> 06:31.167
Oh!

06:31.250 --> 06:33.667
Ow, ow, ow, ow, ow.

06:33.750 --> 06:36.708
Whoa!

06:36.792 --> 06:38.875
Oh, give up?

06:39.792 --> 06:40.958
[ Roars ]

06:41.042 --> 06:42.373
Oh. I don't know why

06:42.397 --> 06:43.750
I even bother asking!

06:44.208 --> 06:46.958
[ Panting ]

06:47.042 --> 06:49.000
[ Panting ]

06:49.083 --> 06:50.144
There's no use

06:50.168 --> 06:51.250
running anyway, child!

06:51.333 --> 06:53.269
- Your grandfather - was just the start!

06:53.375 --> 06:55.686
Soon, I'll have everyone

06:55.710 --> 06:58.042
on earth turned into an animal.

06:58.125 --> 07:00.123
Then, finally, I'll be the most

07:00.147 --> 07:02.167
important person on earth,

07:02.250 --> 07:03.977
and everyone will

07:04.001 --> 07:05.750
have to notice me!

07:05.833 --> 07:07.706
So, you feel like

07:07.730 --> 07:09.625
nobody notices you?

07:09.708 --> 07:11.560
- That's exactly - how I feel!

07:11.667 --> 07:13.394
Well, here, why don't you have

07:13.418 --> 07:15.167
a seat and we can talk about it.

07:15.250 --> 07:16.623
[ Grunting ]

07:16.647 --> 07:18.042
[ Shrieks ]

07:19.292 --> 07:20.792
And stay down!

07:20.875 --> 07:23.625
[ Shrieking loudly ]

07:23.708 --> 07:25.792
Whoa!

07:28.250 --> 07:29.436
A hidden power?!

07:29.460 --> 07:30.667
Bad Bat!

07:30.750 --> 07:34.167
[ Shrieking loudly ]

07:35.750 --> 07:40.125
♪♪

07:40.208 --> 07:41.748
Bad, but luckily

07:41.772 --> 07:43.333
not so smart!

07:45.125 --> 07:46.956
Okay, punching's still a go,

07:46.980 --> 07:48.833
crystal-ing not so much!

07:48.917 --> 07:50.477
- Huh?! - What, I cracked?!

07:50.583 --> 07:52.435
- Diamondhead is not - supposed to crack!

07:52.542 --> 07:54.269
- Ugh, I'm in such - a mess right now!

07:54.375 --> 07:55.292
[ Chicken clucks ]

07:55.375 --> 07:56.935
- Grandpa! - There you are!

07:57.042 --> 07:59.059
- It's a lot harder to be mad - at you when you're a chicken!

07:59.083 --> 08:00.559
- Look, I don't know - if you can even hear me,

08:00.583 --> 08:02.023
- But I don't know - what to do here!

08:02.083 --> 08:03.727
- Gwen's in trouble, - you're a chicken,

08:03.833 --> 08:05.602
- That bat can shatter me - with his screams,

08:05.708 --> 08:07.208
And I'm gonna time out soon!

08:07.292 --> 08:08.375
What should I do?!

08:08.458 --> 08:11.458
[ Clucks ]

08:11.542 --> 08:13.102
- Grandpa, - are you there?!

08:13.208 --> 08:15.227
Oh, I guess all your advice

08:15.251 --> 08:17.292
wasn't so bad after all!

08:19.125 --> 08:20.644
- [ Shrieks ] - [ Clucks ]

08:20.750 --> 08:22.644
- My parents were - never proud of me,

08:22.750 --> 08:24.644
- And I probably say - my evil plans out loud

08:24.750 --> 08:26.477
Because I secretly

08:26.501 --> 08:28.250
want to get caught!

08:28.333 --> 08:29.998
Using your psychoanalysis

08:30.022 --> 08:31.708
to distract me, eh?!

08:31.792 --> 08:33.500
Oh, you're good!

08:33.583 --> 08:35.352
- Hey, you really - think I'm good?

08:35.458 --> 08:37.394
- [ Squeals ] - Too good!

08:37.500 --> 08:38.540
Oh, what about that

08:38.564 --> 08:39.625
distraction over there?

08:39.708 --> 08:40.750
What on earth are you...

08:40.833 --> 08:41.875
[ Zip! ]

08:41.958 --> 08:42.977
All right,

08:43.001 --> 08:44.042
I deserved that!

08:44.125 --> 08:45.208
[ Panting ]

08:45.292 --> 08:47.500
Hold it right there!

08:47.583 --> 08:53.667
♪♪

08:53.750 --> 08:55.875
[ Clucking wildly ]

08:55.958 --> 08:57.102
Ow! Are you trying

08:57.126 --> 08:58.292
to tell me something?

08:58.375 --> 08:59.540
Now that I need your advice,

08:59.564 --> 09:00.750
you're a chicken.

09:00.833 --> 09:02.644
- I guess I should've - listened to you more!

09:02.750 --> 09:03.915
I'll chew with my mouth

09:03.939 --> 09:05.125
full if I want...

09:05.208 --> 09:06.208
Huah!

09:06.250 --> 09:07.917
Blech!

09:08.000 --> 09:09.665
This is the only way to

09:09.689 --> 09:11.375
appreciate the sweet graphics!

09:11.458 --> 09:13.125
Uh-oh.

09:13.208 --> 09:14.750
[ Snap! ]

09:14.833 --> 09:16.000
Ow!

09:16.083 --> 09:17.500
Just a little.

09:17.583 --> 09:19.708
[ Whoosh! ]

09:24.875 --> 09:26.290
What are you trying

09:26.314 --> 09:27.750
to tell me?!

09:27.833 --> 09:29.915
[ Marimba playing ]

09:29.939 --> 09:32.042
World Harmony!

09:32.125 --> 09:37.167
[ Marimba continues ]

09:37.250 --> 09:39.081
Who knew World Harmony would

09:39.105 --> 09:40.958
be the answer to my problems!

09:41.042 --> 09:42.977
- All right, Grandpa, - do your thing!

09:43.083 --> 09:46.625
[ Marimba continues, amplified ]

09:46.708 --> 09:49.708
♪♪

09:49.792 --> 09:51.167
Happy landings!

09:51.250 --> 09:53.352
Now then, child,

09:53.376 --> 09:55.500
prepare for your chickening!

09:59.250 --> 10:00.894
Oh, no, how does

10:00.918 --> 10:02.583
this thing work?!

10:02.667 --> 10:03.833
Sweet!

10:03.917 --> 10:05.375
Ben, Grandpa?!

10:05.458 --> 10:07.415
Really hoping neither of you

10:07.439 --> 10:09.417
got eaten by a giant mutant bat!

10:09.500 --> 10:10.831
Nope, all our chickens

10:10.855 --> 10:12.208
are accounted for!

10:12.292 --> 10:13.792
[ Clucks ]

10:13.875 --> 10:16.542
[ Indistinct radio chatter ]

10:16.625 --> 10:19.250
[ Bat groans ]

10:19.333 --> 10:21.102
- It was a good plan - this time! Right?!

10:21.208 --> 10:22.394
Sure, it didn't go nearly

10:22.418 --> 10:23.625
as well as anticipated,

10:23.708 --> 10:25.310
but at least I made

10:25.334 --> 10:26.958
a breakthrough in therapy!

10:27.042 --> 10:28.311
Well, that wasn't quite the

10:28.335 --> 10:29.625
relaxing evening I had planned.

10:29.708 --> 10:31.269
Who needs relaxing

10:31.293 --> 10:32.875
when you can have exciting?!

10:32.958 --> 10:34.333
I was a chicken, Ben.

10:34.417 --> 10:35.977
- Okay, okay, - too exciting.

10:36.083 --> 10:37.435
Maybe I should've listened to

10:37.459 --> 10:38.833
you about no aliening tonight...

10:38.917 --> 10:40.560
- And about all - that other stuff, too.

10:40.667 --> 10:42.019
- I may not - always get why,

10:42.125 --> 10:43.393
- But I get that your rules - just mean

10:43.417 --> 10:44.894
- You're looking out - for us.

10:45.000 --> 10:46.769
- So, thanks. - -You're welcome.

10:46.875 --> 10:48.706
And?!

10:46.875 --> 10:50.583
stuff was kind of useful.

10:48.730 --> 10:50.667
And I guess your psychology

10:50.667 --> 10:52.309
- It's actually a pretty - good distraction!

10:52.333 --> 10:53.602
Do you need to talk about

10:53.626 --> 10:54.917
your pathological hesitancy

10:55.000 --> 10:56.352
to impart genuine gratitude

10:56.376 --> 10:57.750
towards other people?

10:57.833 --> 10:59.553
- If I say "thanks," - will you cut it out?!

10:59.583 --> 11:00.602
-Maybe.

11:00.626 --> 11:01.667
-Thanks, nerd.

11:02.917 --> 11:06.792
♪♪

11:06.875 --> 11:10.833
♪♪

11:10.917 --> 11:14.667
♪♪

11:14.750 --> 11:15.915
Grandpa,

11:15.939 --> 11:17.125
are you there?!
